{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "krypsos-superagent-v1",
    "name": "KRYPSOS Super Agent Platform",
    "description": "Complete API collection for KRYPSOS Super Agent AI Platform.\nBase URL: https://super-agent-platform.onrender.com/api/v1/\n\nSetup:\n1. Set the 'base_url' variable to your Render URL\n2. Call POST {{base_url}}/auth/login/ — token is auto-saved to the 'token' variable\n3. All authenticated requests use Bearer {{token}} automatically\n\nWebSockets (3 channels):\n  wss://.../ws/tasks/<task_id>/        — live task step stream\n  wss://.../ws/notifications/          — personal notification push\n  wss://.../ws/agents/<agent_id>/live/ — agent live activity stream\nAll channels: Authorization: Bearer {{token}} header required\nKeep-alive: send {\"type\":\"ping\"} → server replies {\"type\":\"pong\"}\n\nTypical Flow:\n1. GET /agents/templates/ → pick a template, note its numeric ID (1–5)\n2. GET /agents/templates/<id>/ → preview template detail before activating\n3. POST /agents/templates/<id>/activate/ → save agent_id\n4. GET /agents/<agent_id>/overview/ → see activated agent stats and recent runs\n5. POST /tasks/create/ → pass agent_id, save task_id, connect WebSocket\n6. If task status = waiting_approval → GET /approvals/pending/ → POST /approvals/{id}/decide/\n7. GET /tasks/{task_id}/ to see final result\n\nTemplate IDs: 1=Email, 2=Research, 3=Document, 4=Calendar, 5=Reporting\nAll costs are returned in EUR (×0.92 from USD stored in DB).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "https://super-agent-platform.onrender.com/api/v1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Paste your access token here after login" },
    { "key": "refresh_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "agent_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "task_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "approval_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "integration_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "member_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "notification_id", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Set from Get Notification response" },
    { "key": "profile_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "user_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "rule_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "invite_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/health/",
            "description": "Check if the server is alive. No auth required."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/register/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"yourpassword123\",\n  \"name\": \"Your Name\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access) { pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.access); }",
                  "if (json.refresh) { pm.collectionVariables.set('refresh_token', json.refresh); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/login/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"yourpassword123\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Login and get JWT tokens. Test script auto-saves token to collection variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Google OAuth Login",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/google/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"id_token\": \"<google_id_token_from_client>\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/logout/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access) { pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.access); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/token/refresh/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"refresh\": \"{{refresh_token}}\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Forgot Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/forgot-password/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reset Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/reset-password/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"<reset_token_from_email>\",\n  \"password\": \"newpassword123\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User (me)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/auth/me/",
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}" }] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 - Profile",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Profile",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/profile/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/profile/update/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Deepak\",\n  \"avatar_url\": \"https://example.com/avatar.jpg\"\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Change Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/profile/change-password/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"old_password\": \"currentpassword\",\n  \"new_password\": \"newpassword123\"\n}" }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 - Dashboard",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Mobile Home Dashboard",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/dashboard/",
            "description": "Returns all home screen data in one call: active agents, tasks today, pending approvals, cost this month, recent activity."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 - Agents",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Agents",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/", "description": "Returns all active agents in the workspace." }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Agent Templates",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/templates/",
            "description": "Returns all ready-made agent templates. Each template shows tools, description, icon, and whether it's already added to the workspace."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Agent Template Detail (by ID)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/templates/1/",
            "description": "Full detail of a template before activating it.\n\nTemplate IDs:\n  1 — Email Agent\n  2 — Research Agent\n  3 — Document Agent\n  4 — Calendar Agent\n  5 — Reporting Agent\n\nReturns: name, description, capabilities (what_it_does), tools, max_cost_eur, already_added flag, and activated_agent_id if already in workspace."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Activate Agent Template (by ID)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('agent_id', json.id); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/templates/1/activate/",
            "description": "Activate a ready-made agent by its numeric ID.\n\nTemplate IDs:\n  1 — Email Agent\n  2 — Research Agent\n  3 — Document Agent\n  4 — Calendar Agent\n  5 — Reporting Agent\n\nReturns 201 if created, 200 if already exists in workspace.\nAgent ID is auto-saved to the agent_id variable.",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Agent Detail",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/{{agent_id}}/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Agent Overview (Detail Screen)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/{{agent_id}}/overview/",
            "description": "Full Agent Detail screen data: stats (tasks_today, success_rate, total_cost_eur), capability bullets (what_it_does), tool chips, recent_runs (last 3 tasks with time_ago + cost_label), and action URLs."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Agent",
          "request": { "method": "DELETE", "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/{{agent_id}}/delete/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Agent Tasks",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/{{agent_id}}/tasks/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Agent Live Activity",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/agents/{{agent_id}}/live/",
            "description": "Live Activity screen: running task with progress bar, queue, live log entries. Poll every 3s while agent is running."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Agent Audit Log",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/agents/{{agent_id}}/audit-log/?filter=all",
              "query": [{ "key": "filter", "value": "all", "description": "all | approvals | tools | errors" }]
            },
            "description": "Filterable audit log for a single agent."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "05 - Tasks",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Tasks",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/tasks/?status=running",
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "running", "description": "queued | running | waiting_approval | completed | failed | cancelled" },
                { "key": "agent_id", "value": "", "disabled": true }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "New Task Form Config",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/new-task-form/",
            "description": "Returns form options for the New Task screen."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Pending Approval Tasks",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/pending-approvals/",
            "description": "Returns all tasks currently waiting for user approval (status = waiting_approval).\nEach task includes approval_id so the frontend can navigate directly to the approval action.\n\nExample response:\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"<task_uuid>\",\n    \"status\": \"waiting_approval\",\n    \"approval_id\": \"<approval_uuid>\",\n    \"agent_name\": \"Email Agent\",\n    \"prompt\": \"Send weekly report...\",\n    ...\n  }\n]\n\nUse approval_id to call POST /approvals/{approval_id}/decide/"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Task",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('task_id', json.id); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/create/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"prompt\": \"Send an email to harideepak.s10@gmail.com saying the Q2 report is ready.\",\n  \"agent\": \"{{agent_id}}\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Task Detail",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/{{task_id}}/",
            "description": "Returns full task detail including:\n\n  progress_percent     — 0–100. Computed from steps_taken/max_steps. 100 only when completed.\n  deliverables         — files produced by the task. [] for Email Agent. [{name, url, type}] for Document Agent.\n  total_steps_estimate — set by Orchestrator when splitting across agents.\n  approval_id          — UUID of the current pending approval when status=waiting_approval, null otherwise.\n\nExample response (waiting_approval):\n{\n  \"status\": \"waiting_approval\",\n  \"approval_id\": \"<approval_uuid>\",\n  \"progress_percent\": 60,\n  \"deliverables\": [],\n  \"total_steps_estimate\": null\n}\n\nUse approval_id to call POST /approvals/{approval_id}/decide/"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cancel Task",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/{{task_id}}/cancel/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Task Steps",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/{{task_id}}/steps/",
            "description": "Returns all ReAct loop steps. Each step now includes generic fields that work for any agent:\n\n  agent_name — which agent handled this step (Email Agent name for now; sub-agent name when Orchestrator is live)\n  title      — short human-readable label e.g. 'Sending email', 'Searching the web'\n  detail     — one-liner e.g. 'To harideepak@...', 'Query: AI news 2026'\n\nExample step:\n{\n  \"step_number\": 3,\n  \"step_type\": \"tool_call\",\n  \"agent_name\": \"Email Agent\",\n  \"title\": \"Sending email\",\n  \"detail\": \"To harideepak@krypsos.tech\",\n  \"tool_name\": \"send_email\"\n}"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Task Result",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/{{task_id}}/result/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Retry Task",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/tasks/{{task_id}}/retry/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "06 - Approvals",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Approvals",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Pending Approvals",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/pending/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Approval Inbox",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/inbox/",
            "description": "Mobile notification tray - pending approvals that need action."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Approval History",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/approvals/history/",
              "query": [
                { "key": "decision", "value": "approved", "disabled": true, "description": "approved | rejected" },
                { "key": "agent_id", "value": "", "disabled": true }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List Approval Rules",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/rules/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Approval Rule",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/rules/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"tool_name\": \"send_email\",\n  \"always_require\": true,\n  \"always_block\": false\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Approval Rule Detail",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/rules/{{rule_id}}/",
            "description": "Get a single approval rule."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Approval Rule",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/rules/{{rule_id}}/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"always_require\": false,\n  \"always_block\": true\n}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Approval Rule",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/rules/{{rule_id}}/",
            "description": "Delete an approval rule."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Approval Detail",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/{{approval_id}}/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Approval Review Detail",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/{{approval_id}}/review/",
            "description": "Returns full context for the approve/reject screen: tool name, input, risk level, task context."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Decide (Approve or Reject)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/{{approval_id}}/decide/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"decision\": \"approved\",\n  \"note\": \"Looks good, go ahead\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "description": "decision: 'approved' or 'rejected'. Note is optional."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Confirm Approval",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/approvals/{{approval_id}}/confirm/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "07 - Costs",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Cost Summary",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/costs/summary/",
            "description": "Monthly + today totals in EUR, plus budget info."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Daily Costs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/costs/daily/?days=30",
              "query": [{ "key": "days", "value": "30", "description": "Number of past days to return" }]
            },
            "description": "Returns one row per day with total_cost_eur and token counts."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cost By Agent",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/costs/by-agent/",
            "description": "All-time completed task cost grouped by agent."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cost By Creator (Me vs Team)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/costs/by-creator/?start_date=2026-07-01&end_date=2026-07-04",
              "query": [
                { "key": "start_date", "value": "2026-07-01", "description": "YYYY-MM-DD (defaults to start of month)" },
                { "key": "end_date",   "value": "2026-07-04", "description": "YYYY-MM-DD (defaults to today)" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Cost breakdown per person. Each row has is_me flag. Summary shows my_cost_eur vs team_cost_eur."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Cost Range (by date + group)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/costs/range/?start_date=2026-07-01&end_date=2026-07-04&group_by=agent",
              "query": [
                { "key": "start_date", "value": "2026-07-01", "description": "YYYY-MM-DD — required" },
                { "key": "end_date",   "value": "2026-07-04", "description": "YYYY-MM-DD — required" },
                { "key": "group_by",   "value": "agent",       "description": "agent | creator | workspace" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Flexible cost report. group_by=agent for per-agent breakdown, group_by=creator for per-person, group_by=workspace for the whole workspace total."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Budget",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/costs/budget/",
            "description": "Returns the current workspace budget (null if none set)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Budget",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/costs/budget/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"limit_usd\": 10.00,\n  \"alert_threshold_pct\": 80\n}"
            },
            "description": "Creates the budget. Returns 400 if a budget already exists — use PATCH /costs/budget/update/ to change it."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Budget",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/costs/budget/update/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"limit_usd\": 20.00,\n  \"alert_threshold_pct\": 90\n}"
            },
            "description": "Update limit or alert threshold of the existing budget. Returns 404 if no budget exists yet."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "08 - Integrations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Connected Integrations",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Available Integrations",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/available/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Connect Integration",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.id) { pm.collectionVariables.set('integration_id', json.id); }"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/connect/",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"integration_type\": \"gmail\",\n  \"credentials\": {\n    \"access_token\": \"<oauth_access_token>\",\n    \"refresh_token\": \"<oauth_refresh_token>\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Gmail - Get OAuth URL",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/gmail/auth-url/",
            "description": "Returns the Google OAuth consent URL. Redirect the user to this URL to authorise Gmail access."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Gmail - OAuth Callback",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/integrations/gmail/callback/?code=<auth_code>&state=<state>",
              "query": [
                { "key": "code", "value": "<auth_code>", "description": "Authorization code from Google redirect" },
                { "key": "state", "value": "<state>", "description": "State token returned by Google" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Google redirects here after the user grants permission. Exchanges the auth code for tokens and saves the Gmail integration."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Gmail - Read Emails",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/integrations/gmail/emails/?max=10",
              "query": [{ "key": "max", "value": "10" }]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Integration Detail",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/{{integration_id}}/" }
        },
        {
          "name": "Disconnect Integration",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/{{integration_id}}/disconnect/",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh Integration Tokens",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/{{integration_id}}/refresh/",
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}" }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Integration Status",
          "request": { "method": "GET", "url": "{{base_url}}/integrations/{{integration_id}}/status/" }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "09 - Team",
